            "job_description": "\u003cp\u003e\u003cstrong\u003eSenior Full Stack Engineer: Develop excellent software! | Cologne | Full-time | Start asap | English (fluent) \u0026amp; German (very good)\u003c/strong\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFounded by the founders of Westwing and Flaconi, at Draxon, we‚Äôre building the future of workforce training ‚Äì combining the power of Virtual Reality and Artificial Intelligence to transform how frontline teams learn in high-risk industries. Our mission is bold: make training faster, safer, and dramatically more effective in sectors like airports and airlines. \u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWe‚Äôre early ‚Äî and moving fast. We‚Äôre backed by leading investors, Point Nine and HV Capital, and already working with major clients. If you‚Äôre excited about shaping a company from the ground up and solving real-world problems with cutting-edge technology, Draxon is the place to do it. Joining our team now is an opportunity to help build a next-generation company ‚Äì AI-native, innovative, lean and obsessively focused on delivering real impact.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"tasks\"\u003eTasks\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eArchitecture, development, and maintenance of our Learning Management System (LMS) and internal web tools\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eDesign and implementation of scalable backend services using Node.js \u0026amp; TypeScript (Express, NestJS)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eDevelopment of modern frontends with TypeScript (React, Next.js)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eDatabase modeling/management with relational and NoSQL systems, including ORMs\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eDefinition and implementation of API interfaces (REST, GraphQL)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eSetup and maintenance of CI/CD pipelines (GitHub Actions, Jenkins, etc.)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eContainerization (Docker) and orchestration (Kubernetes or similar)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eMonitoring, logging, and performance optimization in cloud environments (AWS)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"requirements\"\u003eRequirements\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e5+ years of experience in backend development with Node.js \u0026amp; TypeScript\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003e3+ years of experience in frontend development with TypeScript and React or Next.js\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eSolid knowledge of REST and/or GraphQL\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eProficient with relational databases (PostgreSQL)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eExperience with Docker, Kubernetes, and cloud providers (AWS)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eHands-on experience with CI/CD tools (GitHub Actions, Jenkins, etc.)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eExperience with testing frameworks (Jest, Cypress)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eExperience with microservice architectures and event-driven systems\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eFluent English, very good German language skills\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eStructured, solution-oriented work style and a strong sense of responsibility\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"benefits\"\u003eBenefits\u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cul\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eModern work environment using the latest web technologies\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eClose collaboration with experienced development teams and AI experts\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eOffice in Cologne (5 days/week on-site)\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003ePublic transport ticket for a stress-free commute\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eFree coffee \u0026amp; drinks\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eFlat hierarchies and hands-on mentality\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ul\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eReady to Join?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eSend us your CV or LinkedIn ‚Äì and a short message on why this is your next move.\u003c/p\u003e",
